page.title: 13PAGE 12 CONTINUED.
page.content: It's run by B.E.T. they sell dishwashers.The Land Registry is Government owned.They issue land ownership documents.550 people are employed in Lytham.Alty's,builder's and agricultural merchants,was opened in 1900.They employ 1 driver and 4 workmen.Saddlers is an engineering company formed in 1944.The site covers 9 acres.The Lytham site started in 1947 they employ 72 people and there are 2 departments.They can build and test machines.The other Land Registry Office,a disused army camp,based in Warton is used to save surplus data. {"Minuet"}is an aerosol factory.It employs 12 people."County Demolition and Plant",clears sites,hires out machines and sells work materials. Nutramix(animal feed),Floriana(health foods and toiletries)and Stanways(car dealers)have existed since 1925.
